    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Henry County was named for Patrick Henry, revolutionary leader and the first governor of the commonwealth of Virginia.  It was formed from Pittsylvania County in 1776.
</p>
    </bioghist>
